It's not like one breed is sadder to lose than the other.Sometimes the choice was easy because of an expected or perceived inherent danger -- like the rescue dog getting burned vs a family pet getting burned. Or a soldier getting killed in Baghdad versus during a training exercise at home. In these situations, risk is calculated, expected, and accepted. Some I I honestly am not sure why I made that chose because the two choices had no difference in my mind they were equally as bad. Sometimes I just felt more sorry for the rescue dog who already had a tough life. The choices were all hard but in some cases one was just slightly easier because of sympathy.
